// BT-2207: E2E fixture for `SystemNavigation unusedSelectors`.
//
// `UnusedPerform` reaches `dynamicOnly` ONLY through `self perform: #dynamicOnly`.
// The dynamic selector is a Symbol literal, not an AST send, so the source scan
// never records `dynamicOnly` as used — it WILL appear in the unused report.
// This encodes the documented `perform:` false-positive limitation: a method
// invoked only via `perform:` is, to a static scan, indistinguishable from dead.

Object subclass: UnusedPerform

  // Invokes `dynamicOnly` dynamically. The `#dynamicOnly` argument is a literal,
  // not a send, so the scan cannot see this use.
  run =>
    @expect dnu
    self perform: #dynamicOnly

  // Reached only via `perform:` above — flagged as a (known) false positive.
  dynamicOnly => 7
